{"id":23695,"title":"Isolated mediastinal tuberculosis: a rare entity.","abstract":"Tuberculosis is a common disease in India but isolated mediastinal tuberculosis in the form of a tumor has not been described in adults. We are presenting an immunocompetent, elderly male who presented with fever for 2 months. CT scan chest revealed an isolated mass like lesion in the mediastinum, extending to supraclavicular area. Histopathology of the lesion revealed tuberculosis.","date":"2014-01-30","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24475683","annotations":[{"name":"Tuberculosis","weight":0.882706,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis"},{"name":"X-ray computed tomography","weight":0.866526,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X-ray_computed_tomography"},{"name":"Mediastinum","weight":0.798679,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mediastinum"},{"name":"Tumor","weight":0.773888,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tumor"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.766341,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Fever","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fever"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.752466,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Chest","weight":0.484729,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chest"},{"name":"Histopathology","weight":0.481715,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histopathology"},{"name":"India","weight":0.427867,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India"},{"name":"Immunocompetence","weight":0.374892,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immunocompetence"},{"name":"Male","weight":0.298818,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Male"},{"name":"Supraclavicular nerves","weight":0.110913,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supraclavicular_nerves"},{"name":"Radiology","weight":0.104746,